<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_bæǧa" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>bæǧa</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>мальва (растение)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>mallow (plant)</q></cit></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Из *%ibælǧa%i; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><lang/><w>балга</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_Даль"/>), <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>balba</w><gloss><q>мальва</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/><gloss><q>проскурняк</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и др. Формы с %iǧ%i восходят, возможно, к <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>μαλάχη</w></mentioned>, а формы с %iv%i — к <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>malva</w></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From *%ibælǧa%i; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><lang/><w>balga</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_Даль"/>), <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>balba</w><gloss><q>mallow</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. The forms with %iǧ%i probably trace back to <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>μαλάχη</w></mentioned>, and forms with %iv%i trace back to <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>malva</w></mentioned>.</etym></entry>